node.text: The world needs the story of @amaqamata. A vibrant part of Netflix’s South African original series, Blood & Water, she represents a new generation of global talent on a global stage. Swipe left to hear her story in her own words.

Photo by Netflix US on July 31, 2021. May be an image of 2 people and text that says 'Ama Qamata is at the top of Hollywood's rising class. She shines in her role as Puleng in Netflix's trailblazing South African teen-drama series, Blood and Water.'.

Photo by Netflix US on July 31, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, child and text that says '"For as long as I can remember, I've always wanted to be an actress. My passion and love for the craft grew as I got older and when realized that I could actually make a career out of it."'.

Photo by Netflix US on July 31, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says '"I'm drawn to characters and stories that I feel represent people of color in a positive light. Stories that don't romanticize Black pain or trauma because I think ve seen that already. I like characters that show us in powerful positions. I'm here for all of that!"'.

Photo by Netflix US on July 31, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'HOW DID PLAYING THE ROLE OF PULENG IN BLOOD AND WATER CHALLENGE YOU? Puleng's journey is not an easy one, portraying her required a lot of emotional commitment from me; went on a roller coaster of emotions but I appreciate going on that journey so much because it grounded me and I believe it contributed to my growth as a performer.'.

Photo by Netflix US on July 31, 2021.
